    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix protocol state machine transition in log component cleanup\n\n### Summary\nThe `unregister_all_log_components` function in the logging subsystem used an incorrect iteration pattern that could cause buffer overruns and incomplete cleanup of registered log components. This issue manifested as memory corruption during shutdown sequences, particularly when dynamic log components were registered.\n\nThe root cause was the function's reliance on `while (lc->name)` as a termination condition, which assumed components were stored sequentially with the last one having `name == NULL`. However, all predefined components have valid names, causing the loop to potentially access memory beyond the component array bounds.\n\nThis fix changes the iteration pattern to properly iterate through all valid component indices (0 to MAX_LOG_COMPONENTS-1) and adds proper bounds checking before freeing memory.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/LOG/log.c`: Replaced while loop with for loop in `unregister_all_log_components` and added proper bounds checking\n"
}